The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, March 23, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Gangtok, March 22: Three tourists from Calcutta visiting Chhangu lake in Sikkim were killed when the Tata Sumo in which they were travelling skidded off the road, rendered slippery by snow. 

 R.C. Mondal and Juma Roy died on the spot. Six-year-old Ankita Roy died on the way to a hospital. Seven people, including the driver, who fell 50 m into a gorge, are now in a hospital here.

 Calcutta: A day before the chief minister?s announcement of the caretaker administrator of the Darjeeling Gorkha Hill Council, the CPM said it wants an all-party panel at the helm. State party secretary Anil Biswas said the CPM does not want ?an individual as the caretaker...?.

 Calcutta: Former state finance minister and economist Ashok Mitra filed a writ petition in the high court on Tuesday challenging the validity of value-added tax (VAT). Mitra said VAT was against the Constitution. Court sources said the petition will come up for hearing in a couple of days.




